<div class="field-item even"><p>Avow Apparel, is committed to respecting the privacy rights of our customers. As you may know, when you visit sites on the internet, the owner of the site has the ability to collect information about you, from your name and address to your shopping preferences. The following is our privacy policy. (Note: For this, and all Policies on this, site ‘Avow Apparel’ refers to the parent company Avow LLC.)</p>
<p><strong>Types of Information We Collect</strong></p>
<p>We have the ability to collect two types of information from people who visit our site: Personally Identifiable Information and Aggregate Information. Personally Identifiable Information is any information by which you can be identified, such as your name, address, telephone number, email address, credit card information, birth date, gender, occupation, personal interests, etc. Aggregate Information is anonymous data such as your IP address and user statistics.</p>
<p><strong>How We Use The Information</strong></p>
<p>Avow Apparel, collects Aggregate Information to diagnose technical problems on its site, to help us administer the site, to help us improve the quality of the pages that make up our site, to provide data to advertisers about the volume of use on, and frequency of visitors to the site, to gather broad demographic information and to improve our site to assure that it is as appealing as we can make it for as many people as possible. Sometimes we share this information with our business partners, and sometimes we permit our business partners to collect the information directly from you, for advertising and promotional purposes. In no event, however, is this information is matched to your Personally Identifiable Information. Avow Apparel, also is able to collect Personally Identifiable Information. This can be done only when you voluntarily submit such information on our site. For example, when you subscribe to an email newsletter, when you order our products, when you participate in our surveys and when you register for contests, and other promotional opportunities provided by Avow Apparel, you are supplying us with your Personally Identifiable Information. We use such information to improve the quality of the content that we provide to you on the site. Whenever we request that you provide us Personally Identifiable Information, we will give you the opportunity to "opt out" of receiving future communications from us. By providing such Personally Identifiable Information to Avow Apparel you agree that, unless you expressly opt out of receiving such information, we may use your Personally Identifiable Information to fulfill the activity you signed up for, such as notifying contest winners or sending you information via electronic mail or post, and contacting you with updates regarding the site. Whether or not you provide such information is completely your own choice. You are not obligated to answer any question that is presented to you. Avow Apparel may also disclose your Personally Identifiable information when required by law or court order.</p>
<p><strong>Changing and Controlling Use of Customer Information</strong></p>
<p>If you have provided Personally Identifiable Information but later you object to the use that is being made of that information (for example, you no longer wish to receive promotional or marketing information about products, services, and offerings from Avow Apparel) you can ask that we stop making use of that information. Instructions on how to unsubscribe to our mailing list will be provided in all electronic mail correspondence (please refer to emails for more information and instructions). Your request will be processed as soon as possible. Please bear in mind that if you do choose to be removed from our mailing list you will no longer receive the offers and information related to your subscription.</p>
<p><strong>Protecting Children</strong></p>
<p>Avow Apparel, does not permit anyone age 12 and under to register on AvowApparel.com for any products or services without consent of a parent or guardian. We strongly urge parents and guardians to participate in their children’s online activities.</p>
<p><strong>Cookies</strong></p>
<p>Our site uses "cookies." A cookie is a small amount of data that is sent to your browser from an internet server and stored in your computer. Generally, we use cookies to remind us of who you are, tailor our products and services to suit your personal interests, estimate our audience size, to allow us to better understand how the site is being used, to track your status in our promotions and contests and/or to analyze your visiting patterns. You can set your browser to notify you when you are sent a cookie, giving you the chance to decide whether or not to accept it.</p>
<p><strong>Security</strong></p>
<p>We understand the importance of protecting the security of the personal information that you share with us. Unfortunately, no data transmission over the internet can be guaranteed 100% secure. As a result, while we strive to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee or warrant the security of any information you transmit to or from our site, and you do so at your own risk.</p>
<p><strong>Links to Third Party Sites</strong></p>
<p>This site may contain links and references to sites and organizations operated and maintained by third parties. Avow Apparel has no control over such third parties, their internet sites, or their products or services. Policies for third party sites and their products and services may be different from the policies outlined on AvowApparel.com. Avow Apparel, is not responsible for any such Policies or communicating those Policies to you. Please read Policies on all third party sites for information regarding the use of such sites. </p>
